# Mock Exam System

Mock Exams simulate real-world legal examinations.

They are high-stakes assessments.

---

# Product Vision

Mock Exams must:

- replicate real exam conditions
- enforce strict timing
- simulate pressure conditions
- evaluate readiness
- identify weak areas

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

MockExamController (Riverpod)

↓

MockExamState

↓

MockExamRepository

↓

Exam Engine Service

---

# State Management

MockExamState includes:

- loading
- ready
- inProgress
- paused
- submitted
- reviewing
- error

Core Data:

- questions
- answers
- timeRemaining
- score
- sectionProgress
- examRules

---

# Exam Types

- Full Mock Exam
- Sectional Exam
- Timed Practice Exam
- Adaptive Mock Exam

---

# Timing Rules

Strict enforcement:

- countdown timer
- auto-submit on expiry
- no pause (unless allowed mode)
- warning alerts

---

# Grading System

- raw score
- percentage
- band classification
- topic breakdown
- improvement suggestions

---

# Review System

After submission:

- question-by-question review
- correct vs incorrect breakdown
- explanations per question
- AI feedback summary

---

# Offline Behaviour

- exams can be pre-downloaded
- submission requires sync when online
- partial offline support allowed

---

# API Contracts

GET /exams

GET /exams/{id}

POST /exams/submit

GET /exams/results/{id}

---

# Analytics Events

mock_exam_start

mock_exam_pause

mock_exam_submit

mock_exam_complete

mock_exam_review

---

# UI Composition Rules

Exam UI must include:

- timer header
- question navigation panel
- progress tracker
- answer sheet
- submit confirmation modal

---

# UX Rules

- zero distractions
- strict focus mode
- prevent accidental exit
- confirm submission

---

# Error Handling

- preserve answers
- recover session if possible
- sync results later

---

# Performance

- must handle large question sets efficiently
- lazy load questions

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- readable exam layout
- screen reader compatibility
- keyboard navigation

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Scoring engine

Timing logic

Submission rules

Widget Tests:

Exam UI

Timer behavior

Navigation panel

Integration Tests:

Full exam lifecycle

Offline submission flow

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating mock exams:

- always enforce strict timing rules
- always implement review system
- always preserve session state
- never allow UI distractions